Print:
"print(Value);"
Value - Variable, Int, String

Variables:
To use a variable, put @ in front (Unless defining). Like "print(@input);".

Define a variable:
"set Variable_Type Variable_Name = Variable_Value;"
Variable_Type - Name
Variable_Name - Name
Variable_Value - Int, String, Variable

Change a variable:
"change @Variable_Name Operation Value;"
Variable_Name - Variable
Operation - Mathmathical operation (+, -, *, /)
Value - Int or Variable

Functions:
Define a function:
"function public Name(Arguments) {
Body
};"
Name - Name
Arguments - EX. (Int a, Str b)
Body - Any code (But defining a function)

Run a function:
"run Name(Arguments);"
Name - Premade Function Name
Arguments - Int, String, Variable

Returning within a function:
"return Type Name as Value;"
Type - Name
Name - Name
Value - Int, String, Variable

